    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="447"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.20 Mission/8–1844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-26T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 26, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>530. War has agreed to the extension of the Ridley Mission until March 1, 1945,
                    but states the Mission will definitely be withdrawn on that date. Please make
                    appropriate notification to the Iranian Government.</p>
                <p>War is notifying General Ridley.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
